exts or in many respects only piecemeal in original publications." This book is written for the nonspecialist who wishes to understand the yeasts, but not necessarily to become an expert on them. The new edition covers recent and major advances in the morphology, physiology, genetics, and ecology of these organisms, which have long been important in commerce and medicine and are ever more studied in the laboratory as prototypical eukaryotes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBiologie. 0aHefeartige Pilze. 0aLeveduras. 0aLevure, biologie. 0aLevure. 0aLevures (Botanique). 0aPflanzen (Botanik). 0aYeast fungi. 0aYeasts. 4aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology. 4aYeast. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aMiller, M. W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMrak, E. M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Science eBook Packagez9783110353549oZDB-23-HSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067486355240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067486356940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674863569423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674863569.jpg  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-HCO  aZDB-23-HSP